The paper deals with the problem of distributed consensus in sensor networks, which is a topic in the field of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of quantized data and random link failures involves information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the design of the quantizer parameters, which involves optimization (cs.DC) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
